cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY 

This paper presents a framework for automated mechanism design, which involves optimization algorithms and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also mentions the use of black-box optimization algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the design of mechanisms, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
